There was commotion at Cheregany MP Joshua Kutuny's home in Hardy, Nairobi after a woman claimed child upkeep. According to a police report at Hardy, "Joyline Chemutai had gone to the said homestead claiming child upkeep" from the MP. "This happened at around 0010hrs where a commotion ensued within Mlima area when an alarm was raised at Kutuny's residence," Police said. In the report seen by the Star on Wednesday, police rushed to the scene of the commotion and heard a lady shouting. "..they heard a lady shouting that 'they want to kill me', in the process, Police Constable Emmanuel Maiyo fired one round of ammo to calm the situation," the report read. "Scene was visited and situation controlled...the matter is under investigations." More to follow